race.comment: GOLD DECREE (8) was out of the money on debut two runs back then again missed the frame last start over 1215m at Kyneton, beaten 2.25 lengths into fourth. Goes up a rung or two but he is capable of playing a big role. MAJESTIC CHOICE (12) was never in contention when 4.5 lengths from the winner in seventh over 1207m at Geelong last start, a less impressive effort than her fourth on debut at Wangaratta the run before. Has the ability to take care of this field. PONTE ARCOBALENO (3) has been kept fresh since finishing second last start over 1300m at Swan Hill. Genuine contender. THE PHOENIX (6) is the lone first-starter in the field and was ridden out to win a recent 1000m jumpout at Pakenham but responded nicely when asked. HOMEWARD (9) could only manage to finish eighth, beaten 6 lengths, at her latest appearance over 1180m at Gundagai after she was well back on straightening. Can improve here.
